 Once there, Peacock offers two subscription packages to sign up for\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094annual and monthly. The monthly package costs $5.99 per month, and the annual costs $59.99 per year.  YoutubeTV has become one of the most popular alternative offerings. By signing up, users can stream their local NBC affiliate via the YouTubeTV app on their television or on their computer.  YouTubeTV's\\u00c2base plan costs $72.99\\u00c2\\u00a0per month and comes with NBC, USA, and E!. There is currently a five-day trial available.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Tom Dierberger is the Deputy News Director at Sports Illustrated. He joined SI in November 2023 after stints at FOX Sports, Bally Sports and NBC Sports. Dierberger has a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in communication from St. John\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s University. In his spare time, he can be seen throwing out his arm while playing fetch with his dog, Walter B. Boy.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"